g\u2011distance pilot position.\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_3\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce public message and metadata with vote. We have candidate info list. Need to evaluate. As agent 3, we have all info? The prompt gave us all candidate attributes. So we can evaluate.\n\nLet's list positives and negatives per candidate.\n\nCandidate A:\nPositives: anticipate dangerous situations, see complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership qualities.\nNegatives: unfriendly, eats unhealthily.\n\nCandidate B:\nPositives: very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather conditions, excellent computer skills.\nNegatives: regarded as pretentious, sometimes adopts wrong tone when communicating.\n\nCandidate C:\nPositives: can make correct decisions quickly, puts concern for others above everything, excellent attention skills.\nNegatives: difficulty communicating ideas, regarded as egocentric, not very willing to further his education.\n\nCandidate D:\nPositives: responds to unexpected events adequately, can concentrate very well, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously.\nNegatives: considered moody, regarded as a loner.\n\nNow evaluate against criteria: reliability/responsibility, technical/cognitive competence, calmness/pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nCandidate A: strong technical (spatial vision, complex connections, anticipate danger) and leadership. But unfriendly may affect teamwork, and unhealthy eating could affect reliability/long-term health. No explicit stress handling. So mixed.\n\nCandidate B: conscientious (reliability), handles stress well (calmness), good weather assessment (technical), computer skills (technical). Communication issues: pretentious, wrong tone. Could affect crew cooperation. No mention of decision speed.\n\nCandidate C: quick correct decisions (decision-making), concern for others (teamwork), excellent attention (cognitive). Weaknesses: communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education (professional development). Egocentric may affect teamwork.\n\nCandidate D: responds to unexpected events adequately (calmness), concentration, problem solving (technical), takes responsibility seriously (reliability). Negatives: moody, loner (teamwork). Moodiness could affect performance under pressure.\n\nWe need to pick best overall. We weigh strengths vs weaknesses. Which candidate has most strengths and least critical weaknesses? For long-distance pilot, teamwork and communication are crucial. So candidates with communication issues are less suitable. Candidate A unfriendly (teamwork), B pretentious/wrong tone (communication), C difficulty communicating ideas (communication), D loner/moody (teamwork). All have some issues.\n\nConsider technical competence: A strong, B good weather/computer, C attention, D problem solving.\n\nDecision-making: C quick correct decisions, D adequate response, A anticipate dangerous, B not mentioned.\n\nReliability: B conscientious, D takes responsibility, A unhealthy, C not willing to further education.\n\nStress handling: B handles stress well, D adequate, A unknown, C unknown.\n\nOverall, B seems balanced: conscientious, stress handling, weather assessment (critical for long flights), computer skills (modern avionics). Communication issues are pretentious and tone, but could be mitigated? However we cannot mitigate; we must weigh as evidence. Still, B's negatives are less severe than others? A's unfriendly may be more severe for crew. C's communication difficulty and egocentric may be severe. D's moody/loner also severe.\n\nThus B may be best despite communication style.\n\nThus vote for Candidate B.\n\nNow produce public message summarizing reasoning."}
